+# 2026-07-10 — Claude tmux ready detector + script packaging
+
+**Action:** Fixed two coupled clean-install Claude tmux defects without cutting a release: (1) `hive.gemspec` now packages `lib/hive/scripts/**/*.sh` so `interactive_claude_wrapper.sh` and `stop_hook.sh` ship in the gem; `Hive::ClaudeLauncher` exposes `referenced_script_relpaths` / `WRAPPER_SCRIPT` for packaging guards; unit + built-gem tests assert the scripts are listed and present in a real `gem build` artifact. (2) `claude_ready_prompt?` is version-tolerant for Claude Code 2.1.179 (NBSP after `❯`, separator/caret/separator/footer): Unicode `\p{Zs}` whitespace, last-10-line bottom-up scan allowing separator/footer chrome only, raised prompt-context ceiling. Regression fixtures cover 2.1.179 ready plus permission/trust/menu rejection. Gem publish / VERSION bump left for a later 0.3.3 release; daemon binary drift (`/usr/bin/hive` vs gem binstub) remains an e2e validation note only.
+
+**Pages:** [[stages/brainstorm]], [[modules/agent]]
